%h3 Giftshare Privacy Policy
%h4 January, 9th 2014
%h5 Please Read CAREFULLY
%p
  This site collects the e-mail addresses of individuals who register with us as well as those who are sent email invitations by other registered users. Additionally, aggregate information on what pages consumers access or visit, and information volunteered by the consumer (such as survey information and/or site registrations). The information collected is used to improve the content and performance of of Giftshare, and is no way shared with or sold to other organizations for commercial purposes, except to provide products or services you've personally requested (example: when authenticated with social media sites through Giftshare your email and other personal information may be disclosed), when granted permission by you, or under the following circumstances:

%p
  It is necessary to share information in order to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding illegal activities, suspected fraud, situations involving potential threats to the physical safety of any person, violations of Terms of Service, or as otherwise required by law.
  Giftshare is acquired and/or merged with another individual or company. If this was to happen, Giftshare will notify you before information about you is transferred and becomes subject to a different privacy policy.

%p
  When you register for giftshare we ask for your email address. Users who sign up are not required to provide further information.
  All information collected is used by Giftshare for the purpose of: identification and authentication, services improvement, contact, and research.
    
%p Giftshare uses third party vendors and hosting partners to provide the necessary hardware, software, networking, storage, and related technology required to run Giftshare.  Although Giftshare owns the code, databases, and all rights to the giftshare application. You retrain the rights to your data.


%p
  A cookie is a small amount of data, which often includes an anonymous unique identifier, that is sent to your browser from a web site's computers and stored on your computer's hard drive and are required when users visit Giftshare.
  We use cookies to record current session information, but do not use permanent cookies. You are required to re-login to your Giftshare account after a certain period of time has elapsed to protect you against others accidentally accessing your account contents.

%p Giftshare may disclose personally identifiable information under special circumstances, such as to comply with subpoenas.

%p As Giftshare is in its early phases of development, this policy is expected to change over time. You will be notified when significant changes to how your personal information is handled to the primary email address specified in your account or by displaying a prominent notice on our website.

%p Any questions about this Privacy Policy should be sent to support@Giftshare.io